{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Restructure the UK Energy Market to Adopt the Norwegian Model of Resource Wealth",
        "additional_details": "We believe the UK is resource-rich, yet residents face record fuel poverty while oil giants report billions in profits. Norway, sharing the same North Sea, has a \u00a31.3tn wealth fund and stable costs. We feel our current \"free market\" model fails us; we pay global prices for our own resources. The Government must stop prioritising private shareholders over national security. We believe transitioning to a Norwegian-style state equity model could ensure our natural wealth lowers domestic bills, not just corporate dividends.",
        "background": "Adopt the Norwegian model: Establish a state-owned energy entity with equity in all North Sea projects. Legislate to decouple domestic prices from global markets, ensuring UK-extracted oil and gas is sold to UK households at a \"cost-plus\" social tariff to end fuel poverty and record-high bills.",
